<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4752622>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 84. Distribution of Cybaeus consocius, C. hesper, C. hummeli spec. nov., C. penedentatus, and C. ubicki spec. nov. AZ—Arizona, CA—California, ID—Idaho, OR—Oregon, NV—Nevada, UT—Utah, WA—Washington. California county names capitalized." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4752622/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4752560>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURES 20–22. Cybaeus spp., males from California (20 C. consocius from Muir Woods, 21 C. hesper from Skyline Boulevard at King’s Mountain, 22 C. hummeli spec. nov. from Skyline Boulevard at King’s Mountain). 20, 22 Left palpus, proximal tip of tegular apophysis, ventral. 21 Right palpus, proximal tip of tegular apophysis, ventral. Unlabelled arrows indicate diagnostic characters (20 right angle forked tip, 21 inconspicuous bifid tip, 23 small acuminate tip and central longitudinal concavity)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4752560/files/figure.png" .

